b'Wild sheep are the pinnacle species for many big game hunters. They make their home in the harshest, most unforgiving terrain in the world. 

Hunting them successfully requires complete commitment of the body and mind, as both must be pushed to new limits to thrive in the alpine. 

Adam Foss lives in relentless pursuit of wild sheep, hunting and photographing them as often as possible. He finds solace in discomfort and thrives in the steeps, much like the animals he pursues.

He embodies this level of commitment on and off the mountain in every aspect of his life. The Wild Sheep book was a natural extension of that, and he wove human and animal legacy in these pages with the same voracity that he takes to the mountains. 

This book captures the spirit of sheep hunting, and we couldn\xe2\x80\x99t be more proud to have him on our team of amazing ambassadors and contributors. Thank you for your interminable effort, Adam. 

We caught up with @fossman8 during a recent sheep hunt to ask him a few questions about our second YETI Presents book, WILD SHEEP, and sheep hunting in general. Check out our story for the Q&A.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cDuring harvest, there never seems to be enough hours in the day. The work is unrelenting, but along with it comes the adrenaline of a new vintage. It\xe2\x80\x99s an opportunity to hone my skills, experiment with new things, and to see what Mother Nature will offer this year. 

Between COVID and the wildfires, this vintage has not been one for the faint hearted. I accept these challenges as an opportunity to be flexible, think on my feet, and collaborate with our amazing wine community to make wines that are consistent with the Passalacqua brand. The damage from the fire was inconsistent and localized.  While our overall grape harvest was significantly less than previous years, the grapes we did bring in smell and taste great. 

At the Passalacqua Winery, harvest is now starting to wind down. All of our grapes have been picked and most of the fermentations from grapes into wine are complete. My body aches, and I do feel worn down by the physicality of this job; early mornings and late nights, dragging hoses, climbing ladders, shoveling out tanks, and the cleaning, cleaning, cleaning. But I am energized by the smells in the winery and the young wines recently put into barrel. I am invigorated by the anticipation of someday seeing these wines being shared around a table full of good food and great friends. 

Stories from the Wild: Winemaker Jessica Boone of @passalacquawinery in Healdsburg, CA takes us through a day in the life of harvest. Photos: @luciannamcintosh'

b"\xe2\x80\x9cA chance to get into the mountains and hunt Elk would be a much needed escape from my busy and connected life. Especially in this crazy year. As I went into the mountains of New Mexico I was focused on enjoying the journey of this pursuit. The importance of this week would be more about the story and not the ending. 

This week was one of the most amazing weeks of my life and every day brought a new adventure. From highs of 94 to lows of 22 with over a foot of snow. Witnessing an elk herd over 500+. The sounds of September sent chills over me as the elk bugggled like I had never heard from the bottoms of their lungs. 

I'm grateful to have witnessed the conservation work that is at the core of @rmef_official\xe2\x80\x99s mission, so that my kids and future generations can experience amazing hunts like I had this past week.\xe2\x80\x9d

Stories from the Wild: Ambassador Matt Pittman of @meatchurch reflects on his week in New Mexico with @rmef_official. Photos: @austin_stapleton"

b'Being stuck indoors is the perfect time to take a journey (albeit through video) deep into the Alaskan mountain range. For us, Leighan Falley has always been an example of someone who manages to find balance in life \xe2\x80\x94 she pilots planes through Denali by day, mothering her children at home by night.'

b'Today\xe2\x80\x99s film is one of our favorites \xe2\x80\x94 a story about Sam, the anything-but-typical duck hunting dog whose heart was always bigger than her interest in bringing in a bird. She did things on her own terms, which is probably why we\xe2\x80\x99ve always related so well to her.'

b"\xe2\x80\x9cAll the fish we were hunting were hanging below 100ft and there was a deep layer of murk down there making it hard to see in those depths and harder to relax within. The surface was not exactly user-friendly either. It was filled with jellies and all sorts of stinging particles that were constantly zapping our exposed skin and making it difficult to breath up and prepare for our drops. None of it was ideal but all of it was quite fascinating. \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
My dive partner @perrinjames1 and I proceeded, trusting in one another while building our own comfort and confidence along the way. We ended up landing our dinner in the depths that day and even had a little fun playing on the surface in between our drops. \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
With so much going on, to remain calm amongst chaos, all while preparing for the next move can sometimes seem impossible. But it's so much less daunting when I'm able to see the beauty in the situation, harness my inner flow and trust myself. \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
Only then, what once was stress transforms into an active mechanism that actually helps me preform. -and what once was fear becomes an intriguing thrill that subtly dances in my belly. And a vibrant buzz comes with it all as I'm able to be present in the moment and appreciate every sensation of the experience.

Obviously things don't always go that smoothly but I do believe that whether in the water or in everyday life, when we feel nervous or stressed but have to perform nonetheless, it's best to harness that anxious energy and know that underneath all those nerves, it's there to serve you. So embrace it and transform it into the vitality you need to step up and simply say \xe2\x80\x98I've got this.\xe2\x80\x99\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
